Instruction: With module 3 still wired in the chain and all switches ON, measure the voltage on the two points of the LED+resistor branch in control module 3: (a) between the LED anode node and the 0 V line, and (b) between the LED cathode node (the side closer to 0 V) and the 0 V line. This will show whether the LED branch is getting full supply voltage, partial voltage, or none, helping distinguish an open LED/resistor, an internal short, or a miswired tap to the lines.
