2026-04-21 01:30:01 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Module 3 switch / series 12V path'] hypothesis_explanation='Measurements show that Control Module 3 receives a proper 12 V between its input + and 0 V lines, but there is 0 V between the + and 0 V lines at its output. A continuity test between the input + terminal and the output + terminal of Module 3 shows an open circuit (very high resistance). Additionally, the LED+resistor branch inside Module 3 is sitting essentially at 0 V on both ends, so it never sees supply voltage. These observations together mean that the 12 V path through Module 3 is interrupted inside the module, almost certainly at the switch contacts or the PCB trace in series with the switch. This open circuit prevents power from reaching all downstream modules and the load, explaining why only the first two control LEDs are lit and the lamp never turns on. Replacing or repairing the switch/series conductor in Control Module 3 should restore operation.'
